Sorry about that I just figured it out, the issue was, I have run

curl -L "https://storage.googleapis.com/download.tensorflow.org/models/inception_v3_2016_08_28_frozen.pb.tar.gz" |
  tar -C tensorflow/examples/label_image/data -xz

which is an old version of the downloaded model, then I used the new following one.

wget https://storage.googleapis.com/download.tensorflow.org/models/inception_dec_2015.zip -O tensorflow/examples/label_image/data/inception_dec_2015.zip

unzip tensorflow/examples/label_image/data/inception_dec_2015.zip -d tensorflow/examples/label_image/data/

This works fine even without -input_layer=Mul --output_layer=softmax I run only this bazel-bin/tensorflow/examples/label_image/label_image

but I don't know why I could not run the old version, I don't even know why I got military uniform (866): 0.684116 score only 0.6 not 0.843 as mention in the example

body:
Sorry about that I just figured it out, the issue was, I have run

```
curl -L "https://storage.googleapis.com/download.tensorflow.org/models/inception_v3_2016_08_28_frozen.pb.tar.gz" |
  tar -C tensorflow/examples/label_image/data -xz
```
which is an old version of the downloaded model, then I used the new following one.

```
wget https://storage.googleapis.com/download.tensorflow.org/models/inception_dec_2015.zip -O tensorflow/examples/label_image/data/inception_dec_2015.zip

unzip tensorflow/examples/label_image/data/inception_dec_2015.zip -d tensorflow/examples/label_image/data/
```
This works fine even without `-input_layer=Mul --output_layer=softmax` I run only this `bazel-bin/tensorflow/examples/label_image/label_image`

but I don't know why I could not run the old version, I don't even know why I got `military uniform (866): 0.684116` score only 0.6 not 0.843 as mention in the example
